We are recruiting! Join us to study chromosome organization and dynamics or RNA lifecycle using single-molecule tracking, genomics, and in vitro single-molecule assays.

We study chromosome dynamics

Solving MANY-body problems in biology at the single-molecule level

A biological physics lab in the Department of Physics at UIUC

We study physical principles underlying molecular interactions and functions inside cells. Currently, our focus is on how gene expression machines work together in the cellular context. We develop new methodologies based on molecular, optical, and computational approaches and ask critical molecule-level questions that matter for living cells.

Learn more

We’re hiring!

We are looking for highly energetic and curious graduate students and postdocs with a background in physics, chemistry, or biology.
